---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="System Integration | Intelio - Connect Your Systems" description="Connect CRMs, accounting, operations, and data systems. One connected stack instead of disconnected tools.">
<main class="bg-white">
  <!-- HERO SECTION: Video Background -->
  <section class="relative h-[600px] md:h-[450px] sm:h-[300px] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden bg-black">
    <!-- Video Background -->
    <video 
      autoplay
      muted
      loop
      playsinline
      preload="auto"
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
    >
      <source src="/videos/system-integration-hero.mp4" type="video/mp4">
      <!-- Fallback if video doesn't load -->
    </video>
    
    <!-- Dark Overlay for Text Readability -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/40 z-[1]"></div>

    <!-- Hero Content -->
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-5xl sm:text-4xl text-white mb-6 leading-[1.2] font-normal">
        System Integration
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-lg sm:text-base text-gray-200 leading-relaxed font-normal max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Connect CRMs, accounting, operations, and data systems. One connected stack.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 1: The Problem -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-24 sm:py-12 px-16 md:px-16 sm:px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-4xl sm:text-3xl text-black mb-8 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        Your Systems Should Work Together
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
        Most businesses operate with 8-12 disconnected tools. Each solves a problem. None talk to each other. The result: data silos, manual data entry, and leadership making decisions on incomplete information.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 2: Integration Patterns -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-24 sm:py-12 px-16 md:px-16 sm:px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-4xl sm:text-3xl text-black mb-16 md:mb-16 sm:mb-12 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        What We Connect
      </h2>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-1 gap-12 md:gap-12 sm:gap-8">
        <!-- Pattern 1: CRM ↔ Accounting -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-2xl sm:text-xl text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            CRM ↔ Accounting
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.6]">
            Revenue Alignment Without Reconciliation
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Deal closes in CRM → Invoice generates automatically → Status syncs back. Real-time revenue visibility without manual reconciliation.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pattern 2: Operations ↔ Finance -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-2xl sm:text-xl text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Operations ↔ Finance
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.6]">
            Margin Visibility in Real Time
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Project costs and timelines flow automatically → Finance sees actual margin. Real-time profitability without spreadsheets.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pattern 3: Customer Data ↔ Everywhere -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-2xl sm:text-xl text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Customer Data ↔ Everywhere
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.6]">
            One Source of Truth
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Unified customer record → Changes propagate → No duplicates. Single view of customer across all systems.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pattern 4: Operations ↔ Communications -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-2xl sm:text-xl text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Operations ↔ Communications
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.6]">
            Context Flows Everywhere
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Support sees project context → Sales sees delivery history → Delivery sees contracts. No information silos between teams.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pattern 5: Legacy ↔ Modern -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-2xl sm:text-xl text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Legacy ↔ Modern
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.6]">
            Old Systems Stay Productive
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Legacy data flows to modern dashboards → No re-entry required. Phased modernization without rip-and-replace.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pattern 6: Custom Data Flows -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-2xl sm:text-xl text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Custom Data Flows
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.6]">
            Purpose-Built Connections
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Any system to any system → Custom middleware if needed → Real-time or scheduled. Flexibility to connect anything.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 3: How We Build It -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-24 sm:py-12 px-16 md:px-16 sm:px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-4xl sm:text-3xl text-black mb-16 md:mb-16 sm:mb-12 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        How We Build It
      </h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-8 md:space-y-8 sm:space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-2xl sm:text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            1. Map Your Current State
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Understand tools, data flows, pain points. Identify highest-impact integrations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-2xl sm:text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            2. Design the Connected Stack
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Clean integration architecture. Real-time vs. scheduled syncing decisions. Plan for future growth.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-2xl sm:text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            3. Build and Validate
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Implement iteratively. Test with real data. Error handling and monitoring.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-2xl sm:text-xl text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            4. Deploy and Transition
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Complete documentation. Team training. Ongoing support.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 4: Technical Approach (Optional) -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-24 sm:py-12 px-16 md:px-16 sm:px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-4xl sm:text-3xl text-black mb-12 md:mb-12 sm:mb-8 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        Technical Approach
      </h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-6 md:space-y-6 sm:space-y-4">
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          API-first architecture. We connect systems through their native APIs when available, ensuring reliable, maintainable integrations.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Middleware when necessary. For legacy systems or complex transformations, we build lightweight middleware that handles data mapping and routing.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Real-time vs. batched syncing. We choose the right sync pattern based on data criticality and system capabilities.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Monitoring and reliability. Every integration includes error handling, logging, and alerting so issues are caught before they impact operations.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Extensible design. New tools integrate cleanly. Changes to one system don't break others.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 5: What You Get -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-24 sm:py-12 px-16 md:px-16 sm:px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-4xl sm:text-3xl text-black mb-12 md:mb-12 sm:mb-8 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        What Changes
      </h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-6 md:space-y-6 sm:space-y-4">
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Connected Systems — Data flows automatically between tools
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Eliminated Manual Steps — Hours of data entry gone
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Unified Information — One source of truth
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Real-Time Visibility — Dashboards always current
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Scaled Capacity — Same team handles more volume
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Future-Proof — New tools integrate cleanly
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 6: Common Questions -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-24 sm:py-12 px-16 md:px-16 sm:px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-4xl sm:text-3xl text-black mb-12 md:mb-12 sm:mb-8 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        Questions
      </h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-8 md:space-y-8 sm:space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl md:text-xl sm:text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            How long does integration take?
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Most integrations take 2-6 weeks depending on complexity. We start with high-impact connections and expand from there.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl md:text-xl sm:text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Will you disrupt our operations?
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            No. We build and test integrations in parallel with your existing workflows. Cutover happens only after validation.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl md:text-xl sm:text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            What if we change systems later?
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Our integrations are designed to be modular. When you switch tools, we update the connection points without rebuilding everything.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl md:text-xl sm:text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Do you maintain the integrations?
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Yes. We monitor integrations, handle API changes, and fix issues as they arise. Maintenance is included in our engagement models.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl md:text-xl sm:text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            What about data security?
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            All integrations use secure, encrypted connections. We follow your existing security policies and can work with your IT team on compliance requirements.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl md:text-xl sm:text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Can we start small?
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Absolutely. We often start with one high-impact integration to prove value, then expand to connect additional systems.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 7: Who This Works For -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-24 sm:py-12 px-16 md:px-16 sm:px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-4xl sm:text-3xl text-black mb-12 md:mb-12 sm:mb-8 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        Who This Works For
      </h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-4 md:space-y-4 sm:space-y-3">
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Growing companies running multiple tools
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Professional services firms
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Sales-driven businesses
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Lean operations teams
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Companies with legacy systems
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 8: CTA -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-24 sm:py-12 px-16 md:px-16 sm:px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-4xl sm:text-3xl text-black mb-6 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        Ready to integrate?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Let's start with understanding your current state—what tools you use, where manual effort exists, what visibility you're missing.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-block px-8 py-4 bg-black text-white text-base font-normal rounded-sm hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors">
        Start a conversation
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Back Link -->
  <section class="py-12 md:py-12 sm:py-8 px-16 md:px-16 sm:px-6 bg-white border-t border-gray-100">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <a href="/ai-integration-automation" class="text-base text-gray-600 hover:text-black transition-colors font-normal">
        ← Back to AI Integration & Automation
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

<style>
  /* Video background positioning */
  section video {
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    min-width: 100%;
    min-height: 100%;
    width: auto;
    height: auto;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  /* Mobile video fixes */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    section video {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
    }
  }

  /* iOS Safari video fixes */
  @supports (-webkit-touch-callout: none) {
    section video {
      -webkit-transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
      transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    }
  }
</style>
</Layout>

